## What Is a 4 Carat Elongated Cushion Cut Diamond Ring

A 4 carat elongated cushion cut diamond ring is an engagement ring centered on a cushion-shaped diamond weighing 4 carats or more with a length-to-width ratio of 1.15 or higher — where the stone's elongated geometry and substantial mass combine to produce one of the most visually commanding ring formats available. At 1.20 L/W ratio, a 4ct elongated cushion measures approximately 11mm to 12mm in length and 9mm to 9.5mm in width, which on an average ring finger (size 6–7) means the stone visibly overhangs the finger on both sides. This is the ring size at which the elongated cushion shape becomes genuinely dramatic rather than merely noticeable.

The 4ct threshold is significant in the elongated cushion category for two reasons beyond face-up size. First, the elongated geometry's finger-lengthening optical effect is most visible at larger carat weights — at 1ct, the effect is subtle; at 4ct, the stone creates an unmistakable visual extension of the finger that reads from across the room. Second, 4ct marks the approximate threshold where cut quality and L/W ratio selection become more consequential because poor cut proportions or an incorrect ratio are visible in ways that smaller stones at the same specifications conceal.

The 4 carat elongated cushion ring is a statement purchase — buyers in this category are not optimizing for subtlety or daily-wear practicality above all else. The ring commands visual attention, creates a substantial presence at social settings, and photographs with the kind of impact that makes fine jewelry photography compelling. Buyers should choose the elongated cushion at 4ct because they want exactly this — the format is the wrong choice for buyers who want an impressive ring that doesn't invite comment; full size context in our [4 Carat Cushion Cut Diamond Ring guide](/4-carat-cushion-cut-diamond-ring) and our [Elongated Cushion Cut Diamond Ring guide](/elongated-cushion-cut-diamond-ring).

