## Frequently Asked Questions

### What is a 4 carat elongated cushion cut diamond ring?

A 4 carat elongated cushion cut diamond ring is an engagement ring centered on a cushion-shaped diamond weighing 4 carats or more with a length-to-width ratio of 1.15 or higher. At 1.20 L/W ratio, a 4ct elongated cushion measures approximately 11–12mm long and 9–9.5mm wide, creating a ring that visually covers the full width of average fingers with visible overhang on both sides. It is the most visually dramatic format in the elongated cushion category, combining maximum carat weight with the shape's finger-lengthening geometry.

### What is The Empty Tier?

The Empty Tier describes the structural inventory gap in the 4ct+ natural elongated cushion diamond segment. The combination of large carat weight, specific L/W ratio requirement (1.15–1.25), and premium cut quality creates a specification that natural mining cannot supply in consistent volume — at any given time, Blue Nile may carry fewer than 10 natural 4ct+ cushion diamonds that meet all three criteria. Lab grown diamonds resolve The Empty Tier entirely — IGI-certified 4ct lab elongated cushions in D-VVS1 at 1.20 L/W are available year-round across multiple price points.

### How much does a 4ct elongated cushion ring cost?

Lab 4ct elongated cushion complete builds start from approximately $5,400 (IGI 4ct F-VS1 + [Petite Solitaire WG at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)). The best-value build — IGI 4ct D-VVS1 1.20 L/W + [Classic Four Prong Platinum at $1,180](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194156?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — totals from $6,980. Natural 4ct H-VS1 elongated cushion builds start from approximately $33,180, natural 4ct G-VS2 from approximately $43,180 — prices change daily, so filter [Blue Nile's cushion search](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for current pricing.

### Is lab or natural better for a 4ct elongated cushion ring?

Lab is the practical choice at 4ct for most buyers, for two reasons: The Empty Tier makes natural 4ct elongated cushion inventory structurally thin and unreliable, and the price differential is 85-90% — a [4ct D-VVS1 lab from $5,800](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) versus a [natural equivalent from $42,000+](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). The visual difference between a well-cut lab and natural 4ct elongated cushion is zero — full context in our [Lab Grown Cushion Cut Diamond guide](/lab-grown-cushion-cut-diamond).

### What L/W ratio is best for a 4ct elongated cushion?

1.20 L/W is the target. At 4ct, the elongation effect reads more dramatically than at smaller weights, making ratio precision more important — not less. The 1.15–1.25 window is The Ratio Sweet Spot with 1.20 as the optimal single number; avoid anything in the 1.08–1.14 no-man's-land — at 4ct that ratio range produces a large stone that reads as imprecise, so always verify the exact ratio number in the stone's specification before purchasing.

### What setting is best for a 4ct elongated cushion ring?

The [Classic Four Prong Solitaire Platinum at $1,180](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194156?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the correct setting for 4ct — platinum's structural strength holds the larger prong loads created by the heavier stone, and 4-prong shows the elongated cushion's full outline without interrupting the corner geometry. The setting head must be custom-sized to the stone's actual millimeter dimensions; specify length, width, and depth when ordering to ensure the correct head size is produced.

### What metal should I choose for a 4ct elongated cushion ring?

Platinum for structural durability — the heavier stone mass at 4ct creates greater leverage on prong tips, and platinum holds prong geometry longer than gold under those conditions. For color strategy: white gold or platinum for F-G color, rose gold for H-I color (neutralizes warmth), yellow gold for maximum color neutralization at I-J color. Color sensitivity is higher at 4ct than at smaller weights because the larger face-up table amplifies any body color — target F-G minimum in white metal.

### How big is a 4ct elongated cushion diamond?

At 1.20 L/W ratio, a 4ct elongated cushion measures approximately 11–12mm in length and 9–9.5mm in width. On an average ring finger (size 6–7, approximately 16–17mm wide), this stone extends visibly beyond the finger's edges on both sides. The face-up area is substantially larger than a 4ct round brilliant of the same weight because the elongated cutting style spreads the mass across a longer, wider footprint rather than concentrating it in depth.

### What is modified brilliant at 4ct elongated cushion?

Cushion modified brilliant (crushed-ice sparkle pattern) at 4ct produces an enormous, continuously glowing soft-light field across the full elongated face — the stone appears to emit a diffuse luminosity that is always present regardless of lighting direction. It is the more popular 4ct sub-type because it photographs consistently in all conditions and creates a permanently radiant appearance. Cushion brilliant at 4ct produces large sweeping flash events — more dramatic but less continuous — and both sub-types require IGI Excellent cut grade for maximum face-up area.

### Is a 4ct elongated cushion suitable for daily wear?

Yes, with the correct setting. Cushion cut diamonds have no sharp corners vulnerable to chipping, and the elongated format's directional geometry actually reduces ring catching compared to a 4ct round or square cushion of the same width. The critical daily-wear requirement at 4ct is platinum prongs — the heavier stone mass creates more prong leverage, platinum's superior hardness maintains prong integrity significantly longer than gold under daily wear conditions, and prong checkups every 6–12 months are advisable.

### How does a 4ct elongated cushion compare to a 4ct oval?

Both create strong finger-lengthening effect at 4ct, but they look distinct. A 4ct oval has a seamless curved outline that reads as an elongated ellipse — elegant and continuous. A 4ct elongated cushion has a rectangular outline with four visible soft corners — more structured and clearly four-sided, with corner geometry that reads from across the room in a way that distinguishes it clearly from the oval — buyers who want elongation with a continuous curve choose oval; those who want elongation with visible cushion-shape corners choose the elongated cushion.

### What is The Elongation Divide at 4ct?

The Elongation Divide — the visual discontinuity between near-square cushions and genuinely elongated cushions — operates at larger physical scale at 4ct than at smaller weights. A 0.15 L/W ratio difference at 4ct translates to approximately 2.5mm in length difference, which the eye reads immediately without measurement reference. This means the no-man's-land (1.08–1.14 L/W) is more costly to land in at 4ct — the stone is expensive, the incorrect ratio reads as obviously imprecise, and targeting 1.20 L/W specifically while verifying the ratio before purchase is the essential discipline.

### Can I find a natural 4ct elongated cushion in The Ratio Sweet Spot?

Yes, but not reliably. Due to The Empty Tier, natural 4ct elongated cushions in the 1.15–1.25 L/W range with Ideal or Very Good cut grade are sporadically available — not consistently in stock. Buyers committed to natural at this specification should work with a Blue Nile diamond consultant to set an alert for stones meeting their criteria and be prepared to wait weeks or months — the alternative, lab at the same specification, is available immediately at 85-90% lower price.

